==English==
=== Etymology ===
Latin ''rāra avis'', "strange bird", Latin pl. ''rarae aves''.

=== Noun ===
'''rara avis''' (''pl.'' '''rara avises''')
# an [[abnormal]] or [[unique]] person or thing
#: ''He was, after all, that '''rara avis''', a Jewish Catholic priest with a wife and children.'' 
#:: &mdash; Jeremy Sams, "Lorenzo the magnificent", Independent, May 16, 2000
#: ''"First of all," Arthur said, "Jack is that '''rara avis''' among Ivy League radicals, a birthright member of the proletariat."'' 
#:: &mdash; Charles McCarry, "Lucky Bastard"

